---
// src/pages/illusions/color-from-lines.astro
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Color From Lines — Optical Illusion Lab" 
  description="Explore the science, history, and visual parameters of the Color From Lines optical illusion."
>
  <div class="py-12 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-7xl mx-auto space-y-12">
    <!-- Breadcrumb back navigation -->
    <nav class="flex text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-400 space-x-2 pb-2 border-b border-indigo-500/10">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Home</a>
      <span>/</span>
      <span class="text-purple-400">Color From Lines</span>
    </nav>

    <!-- Hero Header -->
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center justify-between gap-6 pb-6">
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
          <span class="text-xs font-black px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-indigo-500/10 text-indigo-400 border border-indigo-500/20 uppercase tracking-wider">Color</span>
          <span class="text-xs font-black px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-purple-500/10 text-purple-400 border border-purple-500/20 uppercase tracking-wider">🔴 Hard</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-white">
          Color From Lines
        </h1>
        <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-350 text-base max-w-2xl font-medium">
          Discover how the brain interprets this fascinating color visual puzzle.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- LARGE INTERACTIVE DEMO -->
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-6 border-b border-indigo-500/10">
      <div class="w-full max-w-[600px] mx-auto space-y-4">
        <div class="relative flex flex-col items-center justify-center h-96 w-full bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-950/40 rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-indigo-500/10 p-6">
          <svg class="w-64 h-40 select-none rounded-lg border border-slate-850" viewBox="0 0 240 120">
            <rect width="240" height="120" fill="#030712" />
            <g stroke="#ffffff" stroke-width="1.5">
              <line x1="30" y1="0" x2="30" y2="120" /><line x1="60" y1="0" x2="60" y2="120" />
              <line x1="90" y1="0" x2="90" y2="120" /><line x1="120" y1="0" x2="120" y2="120" />
              <line x1="150" y1="0" x2="150" y2="120" /><line x1="180" y1="0" x2="180" y2="120" />
              <line x1="210" y1="0" x2="210" y2="120" />
            </g>
            <g fill="#eab308" opacity="0.35">
              <rect x="40" y="20" width="60" height="80" rx="10" />
            </g>
            <g fill="#3b82f6" opacity="0.35">
              <rect x="140" y="20" width="60" height="80" rx="10" />
            </g>
            <g stroke="#ffffff" stroke-width="1.5">
              <line x1="0" y1="20" x2="240" y2="20" /><line x1="0" y1="40" x2="240" y2="40" />
              <line x1="0" y1="60" x2="240" y2="60" /><line x1="0" y1="80" x2="240" y2="80" />
              <line x1="0" y1="100" x2="240" y2="100" />
            </g>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Content Split Layout -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-12 pt-4">
      <!-- Left 2-Columns -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-10">
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white flex items-center space-x-2">
            <span class="text-purple-500">🧠</span>
            <span>THE SCIENCE</span>
          </h2>
          <div class="prose prose-indigo dark:prose-invert text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed text-xs sm:text-sm font-semibold text-justify">
            <p>The Color From Lines illusion, also known as the neon color spreading effect, demonstrates how the brain fills in colors across borders where no physical pigment is present. In this visual puzzle, solid black lines cross through colored segments. When the color transitions align, the brain's visual cortex perceives a faint glowing color bleed that fills the negative space between the lines. This illusion is driven by the interaction between the visual system's edge-detecting cells (V1/V2) and color-processing cells (V4). The brain tries to make sense of the local color boundaries by assuming that a transparent, colored filter is layered over the background grid. Rather than displaying sharp boundaries, it blends the color across the white lines, creating a striking glowing neon effect. This reveals that the visual system relies on global grouping and transparency priors to interpret complex layered scenes.</p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Right Column -->
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <section class="rounded-3xl border border-indigo-950/20 bg-slate-900/60 p-6 space-y-4 shadow-xl">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white flex items-center space-x-2">
            <span class="text-purple-500">📜</span>
            <span>HISTORY</span>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-slate-650 dark:text-slate-355 leading-relaxed font-semibold">
            First described by Gaetano Kanizsa (1979). It remains a fundamental demonstration of perceptual processing and cognitive framing.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
